translated: Hökerberg, Gustaf Fredrik Alfred, lawyer, born on September 14th, 1886 in Norrköping to the bank manager Karl-Gustaf H. and Fanny Vougt. Married to Hild Rinander in 1913 and had two children, Gösta (born in 1914) and Dagmar (born in 1918). Completed his exams for secondary school in Norrköping in 1904 and his law degree at Uppsala University in 1908. Worked at a law firm in Stockholm from 1908-1912, and then started his own legal practice in Norrköping. Member of the board of the Östergötland Savings Bank from 1927, and its chairman since 1945. Also a member of the central committee of the bank since 1941 and vice-chairman since 1945. Member of the Swedish Bar Association since 1911, and vice-chairman of its eastern division's board from 1936-1942. Awarded the Order of Vasa (RVO).
